author: Dave Burkey
title: 10th Annual Haunted Forest at The Catty Shack Ranch
text:
Used with permission by The Catty Shack Ranch If you missed last week's opening of The Catty Shack Ranch annual Haunted Forest , boo, boo, boo. No worries though as there is another chance this weekend, your last chance this year. The Catty Shack Ranch invites you out for the last weekend of their tenth annual Haunted Forest Halloween .
The fun starts under the big tent at the front of the property; children of all ages can enjoy crafts and games throughout the night (games, crafts and face painting are included in admission cost). Then take a nighttime stroll to say hello to all the animals and, if you’re really brave, walk through the Haunted Forest!
Costumes are encouraged, but not required. All children will receive a bag of candy at the end of their night. There are sure to be more surprises, so make sure to visit the Catty Shack Ranch for Haunted Forest Halloween!
Catty Shack residents include 24 Siberian tigers, 3 lions, 6 cougars, 4 black leopards, a bobcat, coatimundi, and 2 foxes. There will not be any nighttime feedings during the event.
Haunted Forest remaining days and times for 2015; October 16, 5 p.m. to 9 p.m. and October 17, 3 p.m. to 9 p.m. Admission; Adults – $10, Children (ages 3-11) – $5, Babies (under 3) – Free.
The Catty Shack Ranch is dedicated to the rescue and care of big cats. They provide sanctuary to cats confiscated by the state for illegal ownership, improper enclosures or maltreatment. Educating the public on these beautiful wild cats is their passion.
The Haunted Forest is one of their largest events they use to help fund their mission.
Catty Shack Ranch Wildlife Sanctuary
